Goal: Assign every piece of data to the correct Android storage mechanism.

For every data category, assign a storage type:

Storage Type	When to Use
Room (SQLite)	Structured relational data, queryable, reactive
DataStore (Preferences)	Key-value user settings, flags, simple state
DataStore (Proto)	Complex typed preferences with schema
Internal Storage (files)	App-private files, not browsable by user
External Storage / MediaStore	User-visible media (photos, video, audio)
Photo Picker / SAF	User-selected files from other apps
EncryptedFile	Sensitive files (documents, private keys)
Android Keystore	Cryptographic keys, never the key material itself
In-memory cache	Fast access, acceptable to lose on process death
