Phase 11 — API & Network Planning
Goal: Define every external API contract before any Retrofit interface is written.

11.1 Does the App Need Internet?
State explicitly. If no → skip this phase.

11.2 API Inventory
For every API endpoint the app consumes:

Endpoint: [METHOD] [path]
Purpose:      [What this call accomplishes]
Auth Required: Yes / No (Bearer token / API key / OAuth)
Request Body: [Fields and types, or N/A]
Response:     [Fields and types]
Pagination:   [Cursor / Page+Limit / None]
Cache TTL:    [How long is this response valid locally]
Retry Policy: [Retry on 5xx? Timeout? Exponential backoff?]
Offline:      [Can this action be queued and sent later?]

11.3 Authentication Strategy
State the full auth flow:

Token storage: Keystore-backed EncryptedSharedPreferences (never plain Room or plaintext)
Token refresh: Automatic via OkHttp Authenticator, not manual in every call
Session expiry UX: Navigate to login, preserve intent to resume after re-auth
11.4 Network Client Configuration (OkHttp)
Specify:

Connect / Read / Write timeouts (with values)
Interceptors needed: Logging (debug only), Auth header injection, Error normalizer
Certificate pinning (if required for security)
Cache: OkHttpClient.cache() size and strategy
11.5 Error Response Strategy
HTTP Status → App Behavior
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
400          → Show validation error from response body
401          → Trigger token refresh → retry once → logout
403          → Show "permission denied" message
404          → Show "not found" state in UI
429          → Retry with exponential backoff + jitter
500–503      → Show "server error" + retry button
Network err  → Show "no connection" state + retry button
Timeout      → Show "request timed out" + retry button

11.6 Real-Time / WebSocket (if applicable)
If the app requires real-time updates, state:

Protocol: WebSocket / SSE / Firebase Realtime / polling interval
Reconnection strategy
Background behavior (foreground service vs. WorkManager vs. FCM push)
Validation Checkpoint ✓
 Every endpoint has a cache TTL and retry policy
 Auth tokens are never stored in plaintext
 Token refresh is automated, not manual
 Every HTTP error code has a defined UX response
