Phase 15 — Risk Assessment & Mitigation
Goal: Identify every technical risk before the first line of code is written.

For every risk:

Risk: [Name]
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
Probability:  Low / Medium / High
Impact:       Low / Medium / High
Category:     Performance / Compatibility / Security / UX / Legal / Technical Debt
Description:  [What could go wrong and why]
Mitigation:   [Concrete action taken during architecture/development to prevent this]
Contingency:  [What to do if it happens anyway]

Standard Android risks to evaluate for every app:

Risk	Common Mitigation
Background process killed by OS	WorkManager, foreground services, save state onStop
Memory leaks (context in singletons)	Application context only, lifecycle-aware components
Large file handling (OOM)	Stream processing, BitmapFactory inSampleSize, WorkManager
Android version fragmentation	Explicit minSdk, AndroidX compat libraries, conditional API checks
Permission permanently denied	Settings deep-link, graceful feature degradation
Battery optimization killing background work	WorkManager constraints, FCM for wake-ups
Storage limit (no space left)	Check available space before write, catch IOException
Thread synchronization (race conditions)	Coroutine structured concurrency, Mutex for shared state
Deep link hijacking	Verify deep link origins, don't trust deep link parameters blindly
Sensitive data in logs	Timber release tree that strips logs, no PII in log messages
App size bloat	R8 optimization, WebP images, on-demand delivery (DFM)
Slow startup time	App startup library, lazy DI, baseline profiles
Play Store policy violations	Review current policies for: photo/video, location, accessibility
Validation Checkpoint ✓
