Anti-Patterns to Avoid
These patterns make blueprints unreliable. Never produce them.

Anti-Pattern	Why It Fails
"Use best practices for X"	Vague — coding agents interpret this differently every time
"Add error handling as needed"	Results in missing error states
"Standard MVVM setup"	Leaves architectural decisions to the coder
"TBD — to be designed later"	Blocks the coding agent on design decisions
Listing a screen without its UiStates	Coding agent guesses and produces inconsistent UX
Recommending a library without a version	Coding agent may pick an incompatible version
Open-ended folder structure ("add more as needed")	Results in inconsistent package organization
Skipping the AI Implementation Contract	Coding agents fall back to personal preferences
Starting planning without clarifying ambiguities	Produces a blueprint for the wrong app
